# Java String Functions Quick Notes

## 1. str.length()
**Definition:** Returns the number of characters in the string.

```java
String str = "Hello";
System.out.println(str.length()); // 5
```

---

## 2. str.charAt(i)
**Definition:** Returns the character at the specified index.

```java
String str = "Hello";
System.out.println(str.charAt(1)); // e
```

---

## 3. str.substring(start)
**Definition:** Returns a new string from the given index to the end.

```java
String str = "Hello";
System.out.println(str.substring(2)); // llo
```

---

## 4. str.substring(start, end)
**Definition:** Returns characters from start index to end-1 index.

```java
String str = "Hello";
System.out.println(str.substring(1, 4)); // ell
```

---

## 5. str.indexOf("text")
**Definition:** Returns the index of the first occurrence of the given text.

```java
String str = "Hello";
System.out.println(str.indexOf("ll")); // 2
```

---

## 6. str.contains("text")
**Definition:** Checks whether the string contains the given text.

```java
String str = "Hello";
System.out.println(str.contains("ell")); // true
```

---

## 7. str.equals(str2)
**Definition:** Compares two strings for exact equality (case-sensitive).

```java
String a = "Hello";
String b = "Hello";
System.out.println(a.equals(b)); // true
```

---

## 8. str.equalsIgnoreCase(str2)
**Definition:** Compares two strings while ignoring case differences.

```java
String a = "HELLO";
String b = "hello";
System.out.println(a.equalsIgnoreCase(b)); // true
```

---

## 9. str.toLowerCase()
**Definition:** Converts all characters to lowercase.

```java
String str = "HELLO";
System.out.println(str.toLowerCase()); // hello
```

---

## 10. str.toUpperCase()
**Definition:** Converts all characters to uppercase.

```java
String str = "hello";
System.out.println(str.toUpperCase()); // HELLO
```

---

## 11. str.trim()
**Definition:** Removes leading and trailing spaces.

```java
String str = "  Hello  ";
System.out.println(str.trim()); // Hello
```

---

## 12. str.replace()
**Definition:** Replaces specified characters or text with new values.

```java
String str = "Hello";
System.out.println(str.replace("l", "x")); // Hexxo
```

---

## 13. str.split()
**Definition:** Splits a string into an array based on a delimiter.

```java
String str = "Java,Python,C++";
String[] arr = str.split(",");
```

  String a  = "jas,jas";
      String b[] = a.split(",");
      System.out.println(Arrays.toString(b));

## 14. str.isEmpty()
**Definition:** Checks whether the string is empty (length = 0).

```java
String str = "";
System.out.println(str.isEmpty()); // true
```

---

